What is the Required Vote to Elect Trustees?
�
Provided that Quorum requirements (as defined below in �Voting Information�) have been satisfied, the Trustee Nominees will be elected to the Trust�s Board by the affirmative vote of a plurality of votes cast collectively by shareholders of the Fund.��This means that the four Trustee Nominees receiving the largest number of votes will be elected.
�
THE BOARD OF THE TRUST RECOMMENDS THAT SHAREHOLDERS VOTE �FOR� EACH OF THE TRUSTEE NOMINEES.
�


